b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48453.htm)  [Next](sbe48455.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n7\\. On account of definite rule.\n\nAnother argument for our conclusion is that the text 'Doing works here let a\nman desire to live a hundred years,' &c. (Is. Up. II), expressly enjoins\nlifelong works on him who knows the Self. The general conclusion, therefore,\nis that knowledge (meditation) is merely auxiliary to works. Of this view the\nnext Sutra finally disposes.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 8. But on account of the teaching of the different\none...](sbe48455.htm)\n\n"